		<div class="post-2321 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-animation category-copyleft category-copywrong category-free-culture category-politics category-questioncopyrightorg category-the-interwebs" id="post-2321">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/12/01/copying-is-still-not-theft/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Copying Is Still Not Theft">Copying Is Still Not Theft</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>Over at Techdirt.com, <a href="http://www.techdirt.com/articles/20111129/03463216918/morality-non-zero-sum-games-externalities-why-someone-profiting-off-your-work-isnt-bad-thing.shtml">pro-SOPA/PIPA commenters</a> continue to call copying &#8220;theft.&#8221; Since their main argument for breaking the Internet is fundamentally erroneous, now seems like a good time to re-post this riposte:<br />
<iframe width="640" height="360" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/IeTybKL1pM4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><br />
Please share.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="plus-one-wrap"><g:plusone href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/12/01/copying-is-still-not-theft/"></g:plusone></div><div class="addtoany_share_save_container"><div class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_target addtoany_list" id="wpa2a_13"><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save" href="http://www.addtoany.com/share_save" style="background:url(http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/plugins/add-to-any/favicon.png) no-repeat scroll 4px 0px !important;padding:0 0 0 25px;display:inline-block;height:16px;vertical-align:middle">Share/Bookmark</a></div></div><p class="wp-flattr-button"><a class="FlattrButton" style="display:none;" href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/12/01/copying-is-still-not-theft/" title=" Copying Is Still Not Theft" rev="flattr;uid:ninapaley;language:en_GB;category:text;tags:blog;button:compact;">Over at Techdirt.com, pro-SOPA/PIPA commenters continue to call copying &#8220;theft.&#8221; Since their main argument for breaking the Internet is fundamentally erroneous, now seems like a good time to re-post this...</a></p></div>

<div class="post-footer">December 1st, 2011 |  Category: <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/animation/" title="View all posts in Animation" rel="category tag">Animation</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/copyleft/" title="View all posts in copyleft" rel="category tag">copyleft</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/copywrong/" title="View all posts in copywrong" rel="category tag">copywrong</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/free-culture/" title="View all posts in Free Culture" rel="category tag">Free Culture</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/politics/" title="View all posts in politics" rel="category tag">politics</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/questioncopyrightorg/" title="View all posts in questioncopyright.org" rel="category tag">questioncopyright.org</a>, <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/category/the-interwebs/" title="View all posts in the interwebs" rel="category tag">the interwebs</a> | <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/12/01/copying-is-still-not-theft/#comments" class="comments-link"  title="Comment on Copying Is Still Not Theft">4 comments</a> </div>
